‚ùå Problem in Your Flow
You have this trigger configuration:
  ‚úÖ Trigger the Flow When: A record is created or updated
  ‚ùå Formula in Entry Conditions: Using ISCHANGED({!$Record.Trigger_email_after__c})

Error Message:
"The ISCHANGED function isn‚Äôt valid because 'When to Run the Flow for Updated Records' in the Start element changed."

This means:
You can‚Äôt use ISCHANGED() in entry conditions if your Flow is set to run on record creation too. ISCHANGED() only works when:
The Flow is set to run only when a record is updated, AND
The "When to Run the Flow for Updated Records" is set to:
‚úîÔ∏è "Only when a record is updated to meet the condition requirements"
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
‚úÖ How to Fix It
üõ† Option 1 (Recommended): Remove ISCHANGED() from Start ‚Äî Use a Decision Element
Since you want the flow to run on create and update, do this instead:
  1.Remove ISCHANGED({!$Record.Trigger_email_after__c}) from the start condition.
  2.Use only these in Start formula:
      ISPICKVAL({!$Record.Work_Order__r.Source__c}, 'Online') &&
      ISPICKVAL({!$Record.Type__c}, 'Certificate')
  3.After the Start, add a Decision Element:
    Label: ‚ÄúTrigger_Email_After Changed?‚Äù
    Condition:
        {!$Record.Trigger_email_after__c} != {!$Record__Prior.Trigger_email_after__c}
In the ‚ÄúYes‚Äù outcome path, continue with your logic.
This checks if the field actually changed and prevents false triggers.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
üõ† Option 2: Change Trigger Type to Only Update
  If you're sure the Flow only needs to run on updates, and not on record creation:
    1.Change the Start element to:
        ‚úÖ Trigger the Flow When: A record is updated
        ‚úÖ When to Run the Flow: Only when a record is updated to meet the condition requirements
    2.Then your existing formula with ISCHANGED() will work:
        ISCHANGED({!$Record.Trigger_email_after__c}) &&
        ISPICKVAL({!$Record.Work_Order__r.Source__c}, 'Online') &&
        ISPICKVAL({!$Record.Type__c}, 'Certificate')

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Option                       | Use When                                        | What You Do                                                                            |
| ---------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| ‚úÖ **Option 1** (Recommended) | You want the flow to run on **create + update** | Remove `ISCHANGED()` from start, use `!=` check in a **Decision Element**              |
| ‚úÖ **Option 2**               | Flow only runs on **update**, not on creation   | Change trigger to "record is updated", then you can use `ISCHANGED()` in start formula |


